author: EVAN GRICE Sports Editor
title: Area cross country teams get final pre-district run
text:
Area cross country teams get final pre-district run   
With the district meet on the horizon next week, area cross country teams got one more chance to improve their individual times this past weekend. 
For the Gainesville and Era High School cross country teams, they made the trip to Mansfield for the Mansfield Invitational run Friday morning. 
In the varsity girls 1-4A race, the Era Lady Hornets managed to claim a fourth place overall finish as a team, with the Gainesville Lady Leopards also finishing in the top-10 in seventh place. 
Leading the way for the Lady Hornets was Ashley Downe in 13th place with a time of 12:44, followed by Chelsea Howard in 25th (13:10) and Kenzie Paschal in 27th at 13:12. 
Kenzie Patrick wasnâ€™t far behind in 30th place at 13:30, with Kylie Howard just eight seconds behind in 37th and Kaitlyn Rodriguez one second behind in 39th. 
Hannah Vanhoozer finished in 50th (13:53), with Katie Kolb 53rd (14:01), Elizabeth Zimmerer in 59th (14:10) and Alex Torres 73rd (14:24). 
GHS was paced by Raquel Elias in 15th overall at 12:48, with Gabi Brasher 34th at 13:30, followed by Selenia Carranza 55th at 14:04. 
Leticia Perez finished 67th at 14:20, Yelena Martinez 82nd at 14:55 and Jazmin Tejada 95th at 15:46. 
Meanwhile in the boys varsity race, the Leopards claimed fifth overall as a team, while the Hornets finished in 17th overall. 
GHS was led by Jose Chombo-Martinez in fifth place at 17:35, followed by Dalton Chancellor 34th (18:52), Phillip Stogner 37th (18:57), and Nathan Smith 40th (19:01). 
Nick Welch finished 49th (19:25), and Lliam Gonzales 59th (19:36). 
EHS was led by Matt Muller in 42nd (19:07), Josh Torres 78th (19:57), Austin Bryant 98th (20:47) and Josh Wilson 99th at 20:54. 
Caleb Inglish finished at 21:06, Zac Downe at 21:19, and Kale Hunnington at 22:30 with Hayden Belcher at 23:08. 
Next Monday will see both Era and Gainesville competing at their respective district meets. 
GHS will be running at Celina High School, while Era will be running at Alvord High School with varsity girls set to run at 9 a.m. followed by varsity boys at 9:30 a.m. 
The Whitesboro cross country teams were also in action this past Saturday, taking part in the Melissa Invitational run hosted by Melissa High School. 
The Lady Bearcats took 13th overall in the team standings with Ruth Leach claiming eighth place with a time of 12:22. 
Alyssa Hampton finished at 14:56, Cheynne Matson at 15:00.7 and Anna-Kate Goedecke at 15:00.9. 
Makayla Williams crossed the line at 15:47. 
The WHS Bearcats claimed third as a team. 
Nic Butts won the race at 14:37, followed by Michael Urbina 10th (15:44), Lee Chandley 16th (16:09), Maz Merlyn 43rd at 16:45 and Dustin White finishing in 52nd with a time of 17:04. 
Preston Garrett finished 59th with a time of 17:23, with Antonio Flores 67th at 17:30 and Noah Strange finishing at 21:39. 
Whitesboro will be running its district meet at Pottsboro next Monday with races scheduled to begin around 9 a.m.
